• GraphQL endpoint (request / response structure) : https://intdev-api.starhealth.in/starhealth/v1/api

  • GenerateOtp :

    • url : https://int-api.starhealth.in/sso-gateway/notification/customer/generate-otp

    • OtpType : (REGISTRATION | LOGIN | FORGOT_PASSWORD | POLICY)

    • InputType : (MOBILE | EMAIL | POLICY_NUMBER)

  • Check if user is already registered

    • check user api : Api : https://int-api.starhealth.in/sso-gateway/customer/details

      • if true : redirected to login page

      • false : redirected to registration page

  • Registration

    • Enter all the details in registration form : (mobile ,email , firstName ,email ,DOB , Gender)

      • Generate otp : otp send to entered mobile number :

        • https://int-api.starhealth.in/sso-gateway/notification/customer/generate-otp

      • Register api : All user details + otp

        • Registration with sso : https://int-api.starhealth.in/sso-gateway/customer/register

        • Registration with cps: https://int-api.starhealth.in/cps/v1/customer/create

          • Registration with sso fails : return system error

          • Registration with SSO and cps both success : Login user with SSO

          • Registration with sso success but cps fails : login user with sso and return status code 2001 to highlight that cps registration pending now after login user will be redirected to update profile page here cps registration will happen

  • Login

    • Login with otp

      • Generate otp : https://int-api.starhealth.in/sso-gateway/notification/customer/generate-otp

      • Login with otp : https://int-api.starhealth.in/sso-gateway/customer/login

    • Login with password

      • login api (email+password) : https://int-api.starhealth.in/sso-gateway/customer/login

  • Update profile : update customer profile

    • Mandatory Case : statusCode 2001 in login response :

      • url : https://int-api.starhealth.in/cps/v1/customer/update

      • If profile is present in sso but not in cps

      • Mandatory field like : emial/mobile/gender/dob etc missing in cps profile

    • User want to edit profile : (firstName/ lastname/dob/gender)

  • Customer profile : get customer profile from cps

    • url : https://int-api.starhealth.in/cps/v1/customer/details

    • Fetch customer profile from cps

  • isPolicyHolder : check if user is policy holder or not

    • url : https://int-api.starhealth.in/customer/webapp/api/policyHolder

    • Using customer-portal api it checks whether customer is policyHolder or not

  • viewAllPolicies : gives all the policies of the users as received from the customer portal
    url : https://int-api.starhealth.in/customer/webapp/api/policyList
    The customer portal fetches the policy list from cps and then checks the policy details with the
    core and if the the policy end date is more than 2 years from now or if the policy details are not found
    then that policy is not returned and the rest of the policies are returned.

  • Link Policy :

    • Retail Policy linking

      • GenerateOtp : ( otpType : POLICY )

        • Using policy number search this policy details in partyService :

        • url : https://int-api.starhealth.in/cps/v1/party/search

        • extract mobile number from policy details

        • generate and send otp to this mobile number

          • GenerateOtp : https://int-api.starhealth.in/ent-otp/api/v1/otp/create

          • Send otp : https://int-api.starhealth.in/ent-notification/api/v1/notification/send-sms

        • LinkPolicy : (PolicyNumber + otp)

          • Validate otp : https://int-api.starhealth.in/ent-otp/api/v1/otp/validate

          • Link policy using cps api

            • https://int-api.starhealth.in/cps/v1/policy/policyassociation/create

    • Corporate policy linking : (PolicyNumber + (healthCardNo or employeeId))

      • Using customer-portal api we are link corporate policy

        • https://int-api.starhealth.in/cp/policy/user/linkPolicy/corp

SSM -

AIM: The purpose of the story is to add record of agents who have completed 'COMPLETED 10 SKILLPRO VIDEOS ON ATOM' target.

Logic -

Following logic needs to be implemented -

SELECT AGENT_CODE,
AGENT_NAME,
AGENT_JOINING_DATE,
AGENT_STATUS,
POINTS_EARNED_DATE,
CASE WHEN AGENT_CODE IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE 1000 END POINTS_EARNED,
add_months(POINTS_EARNED_DATE,12) POINTS_EXPIRED_DATE,
'COMPLETED 10 SKILLPRO VIDEOS ON ATOM' TYPE
FROM (
Select
DETAILS.AGENT_CODE,
DETAILS.AGENT_NAME,
DETAILS.AGENT_JOINING_DATE,
DETAILS.AGENT_STATUS,
MAX(date_timestamp) POINTS_EARNED_DATE
from DETAILS
INNER JOIN production.event_tracking.event_tracking_data B ON DETAILS.AGENT_CODE=B.userId
where
node IN ('DIV','svg','path') and pageTitle = 'Grow Pro - Home' and pagePath='/growpro/skill-pro/'
and (ariaLabelText like 'Open in new Tab%' or ariaLabelText like 'Share%' or ariaLabelText like 'Download%')
AND userId IN (
SELECT userId
FROM production.event_tracking.event_tracking_data
where
node IN ('DIV','svg','path') and pageTitle = 'Grow Pro - Home' and pagePath='/growpro/skill-pro/'
and (ariaLabelText like 'Open in new Tab%' or ariaLabelText like 'Share%' or ariaLabelText like 'Download%')
GROUP BY userId
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT ariaLabelText) >= 10
)
GROUP BY ALL
)

This has the record of agent who has completed COMPLETED 10 SKILLPRO VIDEOS ON ATOM' type. After creating dataset with this logic it should be union with existing data.
